content:
OUT! RUN OUT! THAT'S ALL FOR IRELAND! WEST INDIES WIN BY A HUGE MARGIN OF 197 RUNS! As the two remaining batters won't come out to bat because of their respective injuries! On a length, from around the wicket and around off, Liam McCarthy drives it on the up towards cover, where the ball goes in the air but falls down just in front of the cover fielder. Evin Lewis collects the ball on the bounce, and meantime, Andy McBrine has left his crease for a quick run but is sent back by his partner. Lewis makes an aim and hits the bullseye at the bowling end, with Andy falling short by miles.
Andy McBrine run out (Evin Lewis) 28 (21b 4x4 0x6)
Nagging length and around off, Liam McCarthy drops it down beside the pitch to the off side and looks to take a single but is denied by his partner.
Full and drifting on the pads, just outside leg, Liam McCarthy misses his flick shot and gets hit on the pads. There is a mild appeal for LBW from the slip cordon but is denied by the umpire.
Switches to around the wicket and bowls it from wide of the crease, hard length and around middle, Andy tucks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
FOUR! PULLED AWAY! Back of a length and around leg, not a great line to be honest, Andy McBrine shifts his weight to the back foot and hooks it fine to deep fine leg for a boundary.
Very full and around off, Liam McCarthy leans on and drives it back to the bowler.
Floated it up and around off, Liam McCarthy tries to defend it but gest beaten on the outside edge.
Short and around off, Andy McBrine pushes it to the right of cover for a single off the back foot.

OUT! RUN OUT! Ireland lose their seventh and West Indies are on top! Tossed it up and around middle, Barry McCarthy plays it off the back foot and flicks it to the right of mid-wicket, and sets off for a quick single. The fielder there, Justin Greaves, is very quick as he collects the ball and sees to aim the throw at which end, before making a direct hit at the non-striker's end. The fielder seems to be touch short of his crease, despite dragging his bat as Roston Chase gets into the celebratory act instantly. The third umpire is called up and he checks the replays to confirm the same. Barry McCarthy will have to go back.
Barry McCarthy run out (Justin Greaves) 0 (2b 0x4 0x6)
Nagging length and around off, Barry McCarthy goes on the back foot and defends it into the pitch.

OUT! CAUGHT! Straight to the fielder! Roston Chase picks up a wicket on his first ball only! He drops it a bit short and into the batter, around middle, George Dockrell goes back and looks to take on him. He mistimes his pull shot and straight to deep backward square leg, where the centurion of the first inning, Keacy Carty, makes no mistake, as he pouches it safely. Ireland are six down and they look just out of the chase, already.
George Dockrell c K Carty b R Chase 23 (26b 3x4 1x6)
On a length and around off, Andy McBrine comes forward and shows the full face of the bat to defend it.
Back of a length and around off, George Dockrell drags it with a pull shot to deep square leg for one more.
WIDE! Full but down the leg side, George Dockrell misses his tickle shot. Called a wide.
FOUR! PUNISHED! Full and around off, George Dockrell takes a step forward, gets to the pitch of the ball and smacks it through covers for a boundary.
Just short! On a good length and outside off, Andy McBrine swings hard at it and gets a top edge that goes to deep backward point but falls just ahead of the fielder. A single taken.
Nagging length and around off, Andy McBrine drops it down to backward point.

FOUR! STREAKY! Short of a length and around off, Andy McBrine uses his feet and looks to pull it, but gets a top edge that flies over the short third man fielder for a boundary. Also, 150 is up for Ireland.
Slower again, full and on off, George Dockrell drills it straight mid off.
A slower one, full and on leg, George Dockrell goes through his flick early and misses to get hit on the pads.
SIX! SMOKED! Matthew Forde goes short again and on middle, does not bounce that much. George Dockrell once again gets on top of it and hammers it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
FOUR! Smacked away! Short of a length and around middle. George Dockrell picks up the length early and pulls it with disdain towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Back of a length and outside off, Andy McBrine cuts it through point for a run.
On a length and on off, George Dockrell steers it through cover-point for a single.
Another fuller one, on off, Andy McBrine knocks it to mid on.
Overpitched and on middle, George Dockrell drills it to long on for one.
Short of a length and outside off, Andy McBrine cuts it to deep point for a run.
FOUR! Fine shot! Pitched up and just outside off, Andy McBrine drags it nicely towards the deep mid-wicket fence or a boundary.
Full again and on middle, George Dockrell drills it to long on for a run.
Fuller and on off, Andy McBrine pushes it through covers for a single.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off, George Dockrell keeps it out to the off side.
Play and a miss again! Pitches it up and around off, shapes it away, George Dockrell steps across to drive, but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Hits length hard and on off, George Dockrell pats it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on off, George Dockrell punches it to covers.
Touch fuller and on middle, George Dockrell fends it away towards mid-wicket.
Good length and on middle, Andy McBrine flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short of a length and on off. George Dockrell gets on top of the bounce and swats it away to the long off fence for a boundary.
Play and a miss! Goes fuller and on off, shaping in a bit, George Dockrell goes for the big booming drive but fails to connect.
On a length and around off, George Dockrell guides it to point.
Pitched up and on off, George Dockrell taps it to covers.

A massive shout for LBW, but turned down! Full again and on off, nips back in a bit. Andy McBrine steps across to play but misses and gets hit on the pads. Greaves just keeps on running and starts celebrating without even looking at the umpire. The umpire says no as the impact looks just outside off. The ball rolls past the keeper, and the batters get a leg bye.
Fuller in length and on off, Andy McBrine pushes it to covers.
In the air...safe! Hits the length hard, on middle, straightens a bit. Andy McBrine looks to work it away but gets a leading edge that goes over covers and lands safely. They cross.
On a length and around off, Andy McBrine guides it past point for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Put away! Short of a length but angling down the leg side, Andy McBrine just helps it on its way to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Back of a length and on leg, George Dockrell nudges it through backward square leg for a run.
Full again and on middle, George Dockrell knocks it towards mid on.
Good length and on leg, Andy McBrine glances it to fine leg for a single.
Full and on the pads, Andy McBrine clips it through mid-wicket for one.
Fullish and on off, Andy McBrine taps it to covers.

OUT! CASTLED! Justin Greaves gets his first wicket now! He goes a bit fuller this time, on off, holds its line. Cade Carmichael skips down the track to play it, but gets nowhere near the ball and is also beaten by the pace. The ball goes through and uproots the off pole out of the ground. CC departs after making 48 runs and misses out on a half-century. Ireland lose half their side now.
Cade Carmichael b J Greaves 48 (61b 6x4 1x6)
Back of a length and on off, Cade Carmichael bunts it back towards the keeper.
Pitched up and on middle, Cade Carmichael drills it to mid on.
Fuller one and on middle, Cade Carmichael blocks it out.
Good length and on middle, George Dockrell blocks it out. Another wicket-maiden over!
Touch fuller and on middle, George Dockrell drills it back to the bowler.
Hard length and around off, George Dockrell steers it towards point.
On a length and on middle, George Dockrell keeps it to the leg side.
Back of a length and on off, George Dockrell pats it towards covers.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Alzarri Joseph gets his first wicket of the game! He serves this on a good length but outside off. Lorcan Tucker shuffles across quickly to scoop it away, but only manages to get a slight nick behind the stumps, where Shai Hope makes no mistake. There is an appeal, and the umpire takes his time before raising his finger. Tucker knew, and he has to walk back now as Ireland are four down.
Lorcan Tucker (wk) c S Hope b A Joseph 29 (31b 2x4 1x6)

Back of a length and on off, Lorcan Tucker pats it towards point and sets off for the run. Roston Chase throws it at the bowler's end, where it hits Tucker on the back. With 20 overs now completed in the chase, we will definitely have a result in this game.

That beats everyone! Good length and around middle, shaping in sharply. Cade Carmichael backs away to drive but misses. It just goes past the leg stump, and Shai Hope dives to his left, gets a glove to parry it towards fine leg. A bye is taken.
Full and on off, Cade Carmichael pushes it to covers.
A low full toss, on middle, Cade Carmichael tucks it to mid-wicket.
A good bouncer, on middle, Cade Carmichael looks to pull it away but misses and gets hit on the back.
Fuller one and around off, Cade Carmichael lofts it just on the bounce to mid off.
Pitched up and on middle, Lorcan Tucker knocks it towards mid on.
Hard length and on off, Cade Carmichael dabs it to point.
On a length and on middle, Lorcan Tucker nudges it through mid-wicket for a single.
Just short! Short of a length and outside off, Lorcan Tucker cuts it aerially, and it just drops in front of point.
FOUR! DEFT TOUCH! On a good length and around off, Lorcan Tucker waits, opens bat face off late and uses the pace of the bowler to guide it fine to deep third man for a boundary.
Very full and around off, Lorcan Tucker drills it off the toe-end of the bat to mid on.
CHANCE! Should have been taken! Slides in a full ball on middle, Cade Carmichael chips it straight to short mid-wicket, where the fielder drops what should have been taken.
On a good length and outside off. Cade Carmichael knocks it to cover.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Justin Greaves serves it full and outside off, Cade Carmichael leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Length ball, outside off, Tucker punches it to cover for a single. Also, 100 comes up for Ireland.
This is full and on middle, Cade Carmichael drills it to long on for a single.
FOUR! Justin Greaves goes short and outside off. Cade Carmichael makes room and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
Shorter and outside off, Cade Carmichael cuts it to point for a single.
Tossed up,  outside off, Cade Carmichael knocks it to point.
Fuller ball, outside off, Cade Carmichael pushes it to cover.
Wide! Slides it full and down leg. Cade Carmichael misses his sweep.
Flatter and close to the off pole. Tucker slaps it to point for a single.
SIX! Punished! Slightly short and comes with the angle on off. Tucker reads the length quickly, goes back and pulls it over mid-wicket for a six. Also, 50 runs come up for this partnership.
Motie bowls it full and on off, Cade Carmichael makes room and plays it to point for one.
A length ball on off, nips back in sharply. Tucker drops it to cover.
TWO MORE! Short in length and around off. Tucker goes back and cuts it through point for a brace.
Hard length delivery around off, Tucker hangs back and taps it past point and easily takes a couple of runs.
Angling on the pads. Tucker tucks it to mid-wicket.
Bowls it on the driving length, outside off. Tucker looks to drive it away but misses.
Full and shaping on middle, Cade Carmichael turns it to square leg for one.
The arm ball, outside off, Cade Carmichael strokes it to sweeper cover for a single.
Quicker, fuller and on middle, Cade Carmichael blocks it on the leg side.
Too full and on middle and off, this is defended out.
FOUR! Good shot! Cade Carmichael is taking his time, but is settling now! Full and on middle, Cade Carmichael slog-sweeps it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Spills it full and angling on leg, Cade Carmichael looks to flick but inside edges it on the leg side.
Shorter and outside off, Tucker cuts it through cover for a single.
This one nips back in on middle, Tucker guides it to third man for a single.
Goes short and around off, Tucker plays it close to his body and on the deck.
A good length ball, tight on middle. Tucker makes a solid block onto the deck.
Length ball, outside off. Tucker slashes but misses it.
THREE MORE! Alzarri Joseph is leaking runs at the moment. Full and on middle, Cade Carmichael flicks it to deep mid-wicket, on the longer side for three runs.
SIX! Where has this come from? Cade Carmichael meant that! Bangs it short and outside off. Cade Carmichael upper cuts it over third man for a biggie.
A single to end the over as Cade Carmichael plays it to long off.
Very full and outside off, Cade Carmichael leans and pushes it to cover.
Full and on middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
That was close! Floats it very full and on middle and leg. Cade Carmichael fails to flick and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal for LBW but turned down. Just spinning a bit, maybe.
FOUR LEG BYES! Tossed up, sliding on the leg side. Cade Carmichael looks to sweep but misses, and it rolls off the pads to fine leg for four.
Drops it short and outside off, Tucker cuts it past point for a single.
Bowls it short and outside off, it is left alone.
Shorter delivery on off, Cade Carmichael pulls it through mid-wicket for a couple more.
Short in length and outside off, Cade Carmichael dabs it to the man at point.
FOUR! Ireland need to take their chances. Cade Carmichael does take one here. Shorter and outside off. Cade Carmichael bends a bit and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Touch fuller and around off, Cade Carmichael pushes it to cover.
Alzarri Joseph starts with a length ball on off, Tucker taps it in front of mid off for a sharp single.
Goes too full and around off, Tucker knocks it to long off for a single.
Bowls it full and around off, Tucker punches it to point.
Fuller ball on middle, Cade Carmichael plays it to long on for a single
Flatter and outside off. Tucker cuts it through point for a single.
Tossed up full and on off, Tucker gets behind the line and blocks.
Tossed up on off, Cade Carmichael pushes it to long off for a single.
FOUR! Welcome boundary! Jayden Seales keeps it short and on middle, Tucker pulls it hard and past square leg for a boundary. Ireland need more and more.
Short of a length and outside off. Tucker gets tall to pull but misses.
A good length delivery on middle, Tucker defends close to his body.
Bowls it full and on the pads. Cade Carmichael turns it to square leg for a single.
Short in length and around off, Tucker pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
This is full and outside off, Tucker punches it to cover.
Touch fuller and on off, Cade Carmichael pushes it to covers. Back-to-back maidens!
Back of a length and on off, Cade Carmichael dabs it to point.
On a length and on off, Cade Carmichael pushes it to covers.
Beaten! Touch fuller and around off, shaping away, Cade Carmichael goes for the big drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length and on middle, shaping in, Cade Carmichael looks to play but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball lobs to the leg side.
Fuller and on middle, Cade Carmichael blocks it down the pitch.

OUT! TIMBER! Jayden Seales has three, and this is another Jaffa from him! He hits the length hard and on the fifth stump line, gets it to swing back in sharply. Harry Tector gets into two minds whether to play or leave, but gets his judgment wrong and lets it through. The ball zips through and rattles the off pole. Seales is pumped up, and why shouldn't he? He has rattled the Irish top order. Also, a double-wicket maiden for him.
Harry Tector b J Seales 0 (5b 0x4 0x6)

A shout for LBW, but turned down! Length again and on middle, nips back in, Harry Tector looks to play but misses and gets hit high on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW, but the umpire says no as this one is going over.
Good length and on middle, angling in, Harry Tector keeps it out to the leg side.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Tector dabs it down towards point.
Hard length and outside off, shaping away, Harry Tector leaves it alone.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Jayden Seales strikes again! The dangerous Paul Stirling goes back for 26 off 19 balls, and Ireland are in deep trouble now. This is short of a length and just on off, takes off a bit. Paul Stirling stays back and slashes hard at it, but without much footwork. It is a bit too close to the body as well, and the ball flies off the outside edge towards first slip, where Justin Greaves shows great reflexes to take a sharp catch near his head. Ireland are 40/2 now!
Paul Stirling (c) c J Greaves b J Seales 26 (19b 3x4 2x6)
Short and well outside of, Cade Carmichael cuts it hard but finds point.
So close again! Hard length and on off, shoots up a bit and nips back. Cade Carmichael hops up to block but gets a bottom edge just past the stumps.
Back of a length and on off, Cade Carmichael pats it towards short covers.
On a length and on leg, Forde tumbles after delivering that one. Paul Stirling clips it towards mid-wicket for a run.
A low full toss, on middle, Cade Carmichael steps across and clips it to fine leg for a run.
Short of a length and on off, Cade Carmichael dabs it to point.
Fuller one and around off, Paul Stirling drills it off the toe-end towards mid on.
FOUR! Powered away! Bangs this one into the pitch and around off. Paul Stirling backs away a bit, rides the bounce and crunches it through covers for another boundary.
Pitched up and on middle, shaping in, Cade Carmichael tries to drive it away but gets an inside edge towards fine leg for one.
Back of a length and outside off, bounces a bit more than the batter expects, Cade Carmichael slashes at it but misses.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Short of a length and on middle, sits up nicely for the batter. Cade Carmichael gets on top of it and pulls it away to the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Close! Good length and on middle, nips back in, Cade Carmichael looks to push it away but gets an inside edge onto his pads.

SIX! Oh..that is a shot and a half! Matthew Forde lands this short of a length and outside off. Paul Stirling goes inside out to access the off side, extends his arms and carves it over the deep extra cover fence for a biggie.
Touch fuller and on leg, Paul Stirling turns it to the leg side.
Back of a length and on middle, angling in, Paul Stirling fends it on the pitch.
SIX! BANG! Matthew Forde bowls a slower one, full and on middle. Paul Stirling picks it up early, whips it away with the flick of the wrists over the deep square leg fence for a biggie.
Good length and on off, Paul Stirling keeps it out to the off side.
Fuller one and around off, Paul Stirling taps it to covers.
On a length and on off, Cade Carmichael pushes it to covers.
Pitched up and on off, Paul Stirling uses his feet to loft it away but gets an inside edge towards short fine for a run.
Jaffa! Hard-length delivery, on middle, nips back in with some extra bounce. Paul Stirling gets squared up as the ball zips past the outside edge.
On a length and on middle, Paul Stirling blocks it out.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Back of a length and around off, shapes away. Cade Carmichael looks to cut it away but gets an outside edge towards first slip. Brandon King gets both hands on it but spills it out.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Very full and around off. Cade Carmichael leans onto his drive nicely and creams it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! There is the charge again, and this time he connects well. Pitched up and around middle. Paul Stirling skips down the track and lofts it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
BEAUTY! Good-length delivery, on off, holds its line and gets some extra bounce. Paul Stirling stays back to play at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Uppish but safe! Hits the hard length and around middle, takes off a bit. Paul Stirling uses his feet but gets into an awkward position and only manages to chip it just in front of mid on.
Touch fuller and around off, Paul Stirling plays a lovely square drive, but Roston Chase stops it well at point.
Back of a length and on off, Paul Stirling dabs it to point.
FOUR! Gets off the mark in style! Matthew Forde serves this full but angling into the pads. Paul Stirling flicks it away with nice timing through square leg for a boundary.
Pitched up and on middle, Cade Carmichael knocks it down the pitch. A wicket-maiden over!
Much fuller this time, on off, Cade Carmichael drives it well but straight to covers.
Almost another! Short of a length and on off, nips back in again, Cade Carmichael looks to guide it away but gets an inside edge just past the stumps.

OUT! BOWLED'EM! That's an absolute beauty from Jayden Seales! He gets his first of the series, and this is a dream dismissal for him. He lands this one on a good length, just on off, nips back in sharply after hitting the deck. Andy Balbirnie stays in his crease and looks to drive without much footwork and down the wrong line as well. The ball goes through the huge gap between bat and pad to shatter the stumps. Ireland are rocked early!
Andy Balbirnie b J Seales 3 (9b 0x4 0x6)
Full again and on middle, angling in, Andy Balbirnie knocks it towards mid on.
Jayden Seales begins with a full delivery, on middle, Andy Balbirnie drills it to mid on.
Ireland and Andy Balbirnie are underway! On a length and on middle, Andy Balbirnie nudges it through mid-wicket as the fielder chases it down and slides to stop it. Three runs taken.
Just short! Hard length and outside off, shapes away a bit. Andy Balbirnie looks to cut it away but gets a slight nick behind. The ball just lands in front of Shai Hope.
Hits the hard length and on middle, Andy Balbirnie stays back and pats it to mid on.
Goes a bit fuller and on middle, shaping in, Andy Balbirnie blocks it out with a straight bat.
Back of a length and on off, Andy Balbirnie punches it sweetly but straight to covers.
Matthew Forde starts with a short-of-a-length delivery around off, shaping away, Andy Balbirnie leaves it alone.

FOUR! Powered away! Liam McCarthy goes fuller this time, on off. Roston Chase stays deep in his crease and pumps it down the ground to the long off fence for a boundary. West Indies finishes on 385/7 - the highest total in ODIs at this venue.
Pitched up and around off, Gudakesh Motie drills it away towards sweeper covers for one.

SIX! Just over! Short of a length and outside off again. Gudakesh Motie slashes again and connects well this time as the ball flies towards the deep point fence. Cade Carmichael leaps up to grab it but it just goes over his head for a biggie.
Back of a length and outside off, Gudakesh Motie tries to cut but misses.

OUT! TAKEN! Liam McCarthy strikes! He bangs in a sharp bouncer, on middle, takes off a bit. Matthew Forde looks to pull it away but the ball gets big on him. It takes the top edge and goes up in the air towards square leg where Cade Carmichael takes a good catch. West Indies are 374/7 now!
Matthew Forde c C Carmichael b L McCarthy 12 (5b 1x4 1x6)
FOUR! Up and over! Fuller and just outside off, Matthew Forde opens the face of his bat and lifts it over point for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, Roston Chase drills it wide of long on where a fumble allows the second run. Barry McCarthy finishes his spell with 3 wickets, giving away exactly 100 runs.
Good length and outside off, angling away, Roston Chase slashes at it but misses. Oh! The umpire calls it a wide. A marginal one.
Pitches it up, outside off, Matthew Forde slices it through extra covers for one.

SIX! Barry McCarthy misses his yorker and serves a juicy full toss, on middle. Matthew Forde clears his front leg away and smokes it over the bowler's head for a biggie. He has gone for 96 runs now, and this is the most expensive spell in ODIs for Ireland.
A low full toss but way, way outside off, Matthew Forde lets it go. Another wide.
Short of a length and around off, Roston Chase punches it to long off for a single.
Nails the wide yorker this time, outside off, Roston Chase fails to dig it out.
Pitched up but way outside off, Roston Chase leaves it alone. Wided.

OUT! TAKEN! Barry McCarthy gets his third now! He bowls a slower one, full and well outside off. Justin Greaves tries to reach out for it to loft it away, but fails to get any power on that. The ball just loops up towards extra covers, where Paul Stirling takes a dolly. Greaves departs after a quick-fire half-century!
Justin Greaves c P Stirling b B McCarthy 50 (23b 5x4 3x6)

FIFTY FOR GREAVES! His maiden in ODIs, and this has come in just 22 balls. Fiery batting from him, and he will look to finish on a high, too. Pitched up and outside off, Justin Greaves throws his bat at it but gets an inside edge towards short fine for one.
FOUR! Fuller one and on middle, Justin Greaves drags it a bit and lofts it wide of long on. The fielder runs to his right, but overruns it and lets it through for a boundary.

SIX! SHEER POWER! Liam McCarthy delivers a length ball, on middle. Justin Greaves climbs onto it and absolutely dismisses it over the deep square leg fence for an enormous biggie. He has hit that out of the stadium and moves to 45, which is his highest individual score in this format. Also, 350 up for the Windies!
Short of a length but just a bit too outside off, Justin Greaves swings but misses. Wided again.
Hard length and around off, Matthew Forde slices it towards deep point for a run.
Fuller one but down the leg side, Matthew Forde misses his flick. Wided.

OUT! TAKEN! Liam McCarthy strikes! Finally, Ireland gets rid of Keacy Carty, who walks back after an exceptional knock of 170 off 142 balls. A slower one, full and around middle, Carty looks to go for the big slog but goes through it a bit early. He ends up mistiming it high up in the air towards deep mid-wicket. The ball wobbles a little in the wind, but George Dockrell runs forward and settles under it nicely to take the catch. West Indies lose half their side now!
Keacy Carty c G Dockrell b L McCarthy 170 (142b 15x4 8x6)
Short of a length and on middle, Justin Greaves pulls it to deep square leg for a single.

SIX! Makes full use of the extra delivery! This is a low full toss around off. Keacy Carty gets right underneath it and smacks it flat and over the long off fence for a biggie. It was hit with a lot of power, and a cameraman was hit on the head. He is receiving treatment, and we wish him a speedy recovery.
Barry McCarthy loses his grip and serves this full and way outside off, even out of the pitch. Keacy Carty lets it go. It is called a No Ball. Free Hit up next...
SIX! MORE! He is playing on another level here! Short of a length and well outside off. Keacy Carty frees his arms and carves it over the deep extra covers fence for another biggie.
SIX! Tremendous batting! Barry McCarthy bangs this one into the pitch, on off, takes pace off. Keacy Carty waits for it, backs away a bit and slaps it over the long off fence for a biggie.
Slower one, hard length and outside off, Justin Greaves stabs it through covers for a run.

SIX! Easy pickings! Barry McCarthy bowls a juicy full toss down the leg side. Justin Greaves stands tall and heaves it away over the deep square leg fence for a biggie. He is playing a similar knock just like he did a couple of nights ago.
Fuller one but on the pads, Keacy Carty glances it towards short fine for a single.
A wide yorker, but a bit too outside off, Keacy Carty fails to reach it. Wided.

FOUR! Streaky but they all count! Back of a length and on middle, holds its line. Justin Greaves looks to flick but closes the bat face early as the ball flies off the leading edge over short third for four more runs.
FOUR! Put away! Short of a length and angling into leg. Justin Greaves picks up the length early, swivels and pulls it away powerfully to the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Pitched up and on middle, Keacy Carty lofts it towards long on for a run.

Bowled'em! Finally, something to celebrate for the Irish. Oh..wait! The on-field umpire gets confirmation that Liam McCarthy has overstepped. The celebration has been cut short. It is a No Ball, and a Free Hit is up next.  Coming to the delivery, it is fuller and on middle, keeps a bit low. Keacy Carty looks to slog it away but misses as the ball shatters the stumps. He gets a life here and will look to make Ireland pay even more.
A full toss, on off, Justin Greaves drills it to long off for a run.
Uppish but safe! Short of a length and on middle, Justin Greaves slices it away towards the vacant extra covers region for a brace.
Overpitched and around off, Keacy Carty drills it towards covers for a single. That brings up his 150, and this has been a sensational knock from him.
FOUR! A boundary to end the over and it brings up the 300 as well. Shorter and on middle, Justin Greaves pulls it aerially but in the vacant square leg region for a boundary.
Good over so far from Barry McCarthy! A full toss, outside off. Carty just taps it to mid off for a single.
Pushes it very full and around off, Justin Greaves carves it to cover for a single.
Rare dot ball! A slower fuller delivery, outside off. Justin Greaves swings wildly but misses.
Bowls the bumper on middle, Carty pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Wide! Tries the slower one but bowls over the tramline. Carty lets it go.
This is full and outside off. Justin Greaves looks to drive but inside edges it to short fine leg for a single.
FOUR! MORE RUNS! WI are 9 runs shy of 300! Shorter and outside off. Carty rocks back and slices his cut shot through third man and backward point, in the gap for a boundary.
Wide! Well outside off, Carty leaves it alone.
Flat and outside off, Justin Greaves plays it to cover for a single.

SIX! CHANCE! The fielder misjudged in the deep! Tossed up on middle, Justin Greaves slog-sweeps it to deep mid-wicket where George Dockrell hangs near the ropes, takes the catch, but as he falls over the ropes, he fails to loop the ball over and touches the ropes eventually.
Outside off, Carty guides it to short third man for a single.
SIX! Carty anticipates a similar delivery and steps across to this length ball as he clubs it over extra cover for a biggie.
Drags this length ball across the batter, outside off and Carty looks to cut but misses.
Flatter delivery, outside off. Justin Greaves crunches it to deep point for a couple of runs.
Quicker and fuller on middle, Justin Greaves smokes it back to George Dockrell, who fails to hold on. Was that a bump ball, though? A dot anyway.
Flat and outside off, Carty hits it to cover for a single.

FOUR! 16 runs off half the over. George Dockrell is not able to grip the ball. Flighted around off. Carty leans and cracks it to deep cover. The fielder runs to his left, gets behind the ball, but it slips through and hits the ropes.
SIX! Consecutive sixes! Carty is on a roll! Floated full on middle, Carty makes himself big and thumps it to long on for a six. Such a good strike.
SIX! First ball and hits like he never left the ground. Tossed up on off, Carty smashes it down to long off and it goes the distance.
Goes wide of the crease and forces it full and on off, Carty knocks it to cover for one.
Slides across a full ball, outside off, Justin Greaves plays it past cover for a single.
An arm ball full and around off, Justin Greaves mistimes his flick back to Tector.
FOUR! 250 up for West Indies! Slower in the air, full and on middle, Justin Greaves lofts it straight down the ground for a boundary.
Pushes it full and wide of off. Justin Greaves drives it back to the bowler.
Very full and outside off, Carty drives it to long off for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Excellent catch by Jordan Neill! Floats it full and on middle, Amir Jangoo tries to go down the ground but toe ends his shot to long off, where Jordan Neill runs across, slides to his left and takes a serious catch. Ireland still have a chance to pull things back and make a difference.
Amir Jangoo c J Neill b G Dockrell 22 (36b 0x4 1x6)
Fuller and wide of off. Amir Jangoo plays it square on the off side for a couple of runs.
Very full and on middle, Amir Jangoo pushes it back to the bowler. George Dockrell throws the ball in the air, but it is a bump ball.
Tossed up, outside off, Carty strokes it through covers for one more.
Slides it full and down the leg side. Amir Jangoo sweeps it to short fine leg for one.
Tossed up, outside off, Carty slaps it through point for a single.
Short and outside off, Amir Jangoo cuts it but straight to backward point.
Slower through the air, tempting length and around off, Keacy Carty goes on the back foot and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Floated it up and around off, Amir Jangoo clips it towards mid-wicket for one.
Just short! Full and on the pads, Keacy Carty just uses his wrists to flick it aerially towards deep square leg but the ball lands before the incoming fielder. A single taken.
Nagging length and well outside off, Amir Jangoo moves in his crease and cuts it to sweeper cover for one.
Tossed it up  and around off, Amir Jangoo goes on his knees and looks to sweep it but misses.
FOUR! DEFT TOUCH! Hard length and down the leg side, Keacy Carty shuffles across in his crease and gets some desired bat on it to help it on its way to deep fine leg for a boundary.
Hard length and outside off, Amir Jangoo cuts it to deep point for a single.
Short of a length and around off, Keacy Carty pullls it down to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! CRACKING SHOT! Much fuller and outside off, Keacy Carty comes forward and drives it hard through covers for a boundary.
Into the pitch, a bit full and outside off, Keacy Carty drives it but straight to extra cover.
Hard length and around off, Amir Jangoo runs it down to deep third man for a single.
Full and around middle, Amir Jangoo nudges it to long on for one.

Short and around middle, Keacy Carty goes back and nudges it towards deep backward square leg. He takes three runs as the fielder in the deep makes a bit of fumble in collecting the ball after chasing it.

FOUR! BACK-TO-BACK HUNDREDS FOR KEACY CARTY! Touch short and outside off, Carty slashes at it off the outer half of the bat and the ball flies it to deep third man for a boundary as he completes his milestone (3rd ODI century). He takes off his helmet and soaks up the applause. A great inning!
Nagging length and around off, Keacy Carty drops it down towards mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Dragged length and outside off, turns in a bit, Keacy Carty looks to cut it off the back foot but misses.
FOUR! SOME STYLE TO START AFTER THE BREAK! Tossed it up and outside off, Keacy Carty drives it through covers for a boundary. He moves to 97 now.
Touch full but on the pads, Carty nudges it towards mid on and takes a quick single to retain the strike.
WIDE! On a length but down the leg side. Called a wide.

SIX! STREAKY BUT CARTY WON'T MIND IT! Hard length and drifting down the leg side, Keacy Carty swivels and looks to pull it but gets a top edge that flies over the deep fine leg fence for a biggie. He is in the 90s now.
Hard length and around off, Amir Jangoo punches it through cover point for one.
SIX! BREAKS THE SHACKLES! Over-pitched, and a bit outside off, Amir Jangoo comes forward and launches it down the ground for a biggie. Also, 200 comes up for WI.
Back of a length and around middle, Keacy Carty goes back, uses his wrists and turns it to deep square leg for one.
On a length and around off, Keacy Carty defends it back to the bowler.
Nagging length and around off, Keacy Carty punches it through covers for one.

Good running between the wickets! Short and a bit outside off, Amir Jangoo slashes it through the outer half the bat towards short third and runs off for a quick single. The fielder throws it to the bowler but Amir makes it to the crease in time.
From around the wicket again to the left-hander, full and around off, Amir Jangoo defends it back to the bowler.
Floated it up and around off, Keacy Carty goes on his knees and sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Dragged length and a bit outside off, Amir Jangoo goes on the back foot and slices it through covers for a single.
Tossed it up and around off, Amir Jangoo drops it down to cover off the back foot.
Hard length and outside off, Keacy Carty swings hard at it but misses. He isn't happy with himself as he has missed out on a freebie.
NO BALL! On a good length and outside off, Keacy Carty cuts it towards point. Oh, Josh Little has overstepped, and this is called a No Ball! A free-hit is coming up!
Full and around middle, Amir Jangoo mistimes his flick shot to deep fine leg for a single off the inner half of the bat.
Nagging length and around off, Amir Jangoo defends it.

OUCH! It will hurt for sure! Josh Little hits the deck hard and bowls it on a hard length and attacks the body of the batter. Amir Jangoo swivels on his toes and looks to pull it but misses and gets hit on the stomach.
Slightly fuller and outside off, Carty punches it through covers for a single.
On a good length and around off, Keacy Carty backs away and looks to cut it but gets cramped up for the room and ends up chopping it out towards cover off the bottom part of the bat.
A bit quicker and flatter, around off, Keacy Carty cuts it through covers for one to end the over.
Dragged length and around off, Amir Jangoo fetches it out to long on for a single.
Similar line and length, around off, Amir Jangoo comes forward to defend it towards cover.
Tossed it up and around off, Amir Jangoo blocks it out to the off side.
Nagging length and around off, Amir Jangoo comes forward and defends it to cover.
Tossed it up and around off, Keacy Carty tucks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Touch short and around off, Amir Jangoo drops it down to mid off.
Attacks the stumps and on a length, Amir Jangoo plays it out to the off side for no run.
On a length and around middle, Keacy Carty tucks it towards square leg for one.
Nagging length and around off, Keacy Carty defends it.
FOUR! TOP SHOT! Touch short and around off, Keacy Carty clears out his front leg away a bit, goes on the back foot and pulls it hard through the gap at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Back of a length and around off, Keacy Carty drops it down towards cover.
Floated it up and around off, Amir Jangoo takkes a big stride forward and defends it.
Tempting length and around off, Keacy Carty goes back and punches it to long off for a single.
Full and around middle, Amir turns it towards mid on and takes a single.
Nagging length and around off, Amir Jangoo drops it down towards cover.

Big appeal for LBW but is turned down! From around the wicket, full and around middle, Amir Jangoo comes forward to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit on the front pad. A very close call, though.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Keacy Carty goes on the back foot and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Nagging length and around off, Amir Jangoo blocks it off.
Leg bye! Shortish, into the pitch and around leg, Carty hops up and misses his tickle shot. The ball clips his thigh pad and goes towards square leg for a leg bye.

SIX! Keacy Carty makes full use of that freebie! Back of a length and around off, Carty goes back, clears out his front leg away and muscles it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie. Stand and deliver stuff!

BEAUTY! On a length and in that channel outside off, Keacy Carty looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge. Uh...Oh! Josh Little has overstepped and this is called a No Ball. A free-hit is coming up!
On a good length and a bit outside off, as well, Keacy Carty stands tall and cuts it to the right of deep third man for a couple of runs.
Hard length and around off, Amir Jangoo punches it to wide of cover for a single.
Back of a length and angles into the body of the batter, Amir Jangoo hops up a bit and drops it down towards mid-wicket.
Quicker, full and on leg, Amir Jangoo clips it to mid-wicket for one.
Slows it up, full and on middle, Amir Jangoo fends it away.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Amir Jangoo blocks it out.

OUT! TAKEN! Andy McBrine strikes and gets a huge wicket for Ireland! The big 137- stand has been broken. This is flatter, short and on middle, skids through a bit. Shai Hope moves back to pull it away towards mid-wicket, but gets a bit cramped up. He ends up hitting it much straighter and flatter towards long on, where Thomas Mayes comes forward and dives to take a fantastic catch. Hope goes back for a well-made 75, and West Indies are 168/3!
Shai Hope (c) c sub Thomas Mayes b Andy McBrine 75 (75b 9x4 2x6)
Flighted, full and on middle, Shai Hope turns it to the leg side.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Keacy Carty sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Classy! Overpitched and on middle. Shai Hope presents the full face of the bat and plays a beautiful on drive. Barry McCarthy at mid on dives to his left, but the ball goes through for a boundary.
Short of a length and on middle, Keacy Carty pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
On a length and on leg, Shai Hope clips it through square leg for a single.
Good length and on off, Shai Hope pats it towards short covers.
Swing and a miss! Pitched up and on off, shapes away a touch. Shai Hope has a big swing at it but misses.
Bangs in a bouncer, on middle, Shai Hope ducks under it.
Looped up, full and on middle, Shai Hope eases it to long on for one.
FOUR! Nice shot! Flighted, full and on middle. Shai Hope goes down on one knee and nails the slog sweep in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Short and on middle, Keacy Carty clips it through square leg for a single.
Floated, full and on middle, Keacy Carty pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter, short and on off, Keacy Carty swats it to the left of short covers.
Short and on middle, Keacy Carty pats it towards the bowler.
Short of a length and on middle, Shai Hope leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Good-length delivery, on the fifth stump line, holds its line, Shai Hope looks to push at it but gets beaten on the outside edge this time.
FOUR! Streaky! Liam McCarthy bangs this one into the pitch, on off, takes off a bit and shapes away. Shai Hope stays back and has a poke at it but gets an outside edge past the keeper for a boundary.
Touch fuller and on middle, Keacy Carty clips it through square leg for one.

FOUR! Was that a chance? Maybe a half-chance. Short of a length and outside off. Keacy Carty cuts it away aerially towards backward point. Harry Tector gets down a bit too late, and it just falls ahead and goes through his legs for a boundary.
On a length and on middle, Keacy Carty nudges it to mid-wicket.
Another short delivery, on off, Keacy Carty guides it towards point for a run.
Floated, full and on middle, Keacy Carty tucks it to mid-wicket.
Quicker one, short and on off, turns in, Keacy Carty pats it to short covers.
Short again and on middle, Keacy Carty punches it towards mid on.
A bit short and on middle, Shai Hope clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, full and on off, turns in, Shai Hope knocks it back to the bowler.
Looped up, full and on middle, Shai Hope eases it to long off for one more.
Goes short again, on leg, Keacy Carty flicks it through square leg for one.
Slows it up, full and on middle, Keacy Carty fends it to the off side.
Drags his length back, on off, Shai Hope pats it to long off for a run.
Flatter, short but well outside off, Shai Hope leaves it alone. Wided.
Tossed up, full and on off, Shai Hope pushes it to short covers.
Short and on off, Keacy Carty punches it to long off for a single.
Floated, full and on leg, Keacy Carty drills it to long on for a run.
Quicker short and on off, Keacy Carty steers it to backward point for one.
Flighted, full and middle, Shai Hope eases it to long on for a single.
SIX! SMOKED! Harry Tector drops it very short and on middle. Shai Hope quickly shifts his weight on the back foot and hammers it over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Short again and around off, Shai Hope punches it to covers.
Short and on middle, Shai Hope pats it back to the bowler.
Slows it up, full and on middle, Keacy Carty tucks it to the leg side.
Floated, full and on middle, Keacy Carty fends it off the front foot.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR CARTY! A fantastic ton in the last game, and he has followed it up with an excellent half-century. George Dockrell bowls this short and on the pads. Keacy Carty glances it away towards short fine, where the fielder dives over the ball and lets it through for a boundary. That also brings up the 100-run stand between these two batters.
Flighted, full and on off, Keacy Carty drives it wide of long off for a couple of runs.
Floated, full and on off, Keacy Carty pushes it to covers.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Shai Hope works it off the inside half of the bat through square leg for a single.
FIFTY FOR HOPE! A fine knock from Hope, and he has looked in control of things here. He will want to make it big now. Flatter, full and on middle, Shai Hope drills it to long on for a run.
Flighted, full and on middle, Shai Hope clips it to mid-wicket.
SIX! SHORT AND PUNISHED! Andy McBrine bowls a half-tracker, on middle. Shai Hope rocks back quickly and whacks it over the deep square leg fence. He has hit it out of the park. New Ball Please!
Short again and on leg, Keacy Carty punches it to long on for a run.
Short and on middle, Shai Hope nudges it through mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Shai Hope blocks it out.
Short of a length and on off, Shai Hope dabs it through point for one.

Wow..that is an excellent stop from the debutant! Barry McCarthy bangs this one short and around leg. Shai Hope looks to hook it away but gets a tope edge wide of fine leg. Jordan Neill runs to his right and flies to slap the ball back inside the field with his right hand. He lands very hard on his right shoulder and looks in a bit of pain. Two runs taken.
Pitched up, on middle, shaping in, Keacy Carty flicks it off the toe-end of the bat through mid-wicket for a run.
Touch fuller and on middle, Shai Hope taps it towards covers for a single. Nelson is on the board for Windies.
Back of a length and outside off, Shai Hope leaves it alone.
FOUR! Glorious shot! Much fuller and around off. Shai Hope plants his front foot forward, keeps his head still and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Andy McBrine from around the wicket bowls it full and on middle, played back to the bowler.
Very full and on middle, Hope drills it to long on for a single.
Flatter and around off, turns in. Hope turns it to mid-wicket.
Another single as Carty works it to deep mid-wicket for one more.
Tossed up on middle, Hope turns it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off, Carty drives it to covers for a single.
Length ball on middle, Hope blocks it out.
Tails back in one into the surface on middle, Carty nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Good length delivery angling on middle, Carty leans and blocks it out.
Fuller delivery, outside off, nips in. Carty pushes it to cover.
Length ball, well outside off. Hope frees his arms and slaps it to cover for a single.
Barry McCarthy serves it full and outside off, Hope knocks it to cover.
Slightly short and around off, Carty punches it to cover.
100 up for West Indies! Tossed up on middle, Hope goes back and nudges it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Flatter and around off, turns in. Carty works it to long on for one run.
Tossed up on middle, Carty bunts it to mid-wicket.
Floats it full and on middle, Hope plays with soft hands on the leg side for a run.
Andy McBrine bowls it full and spinning on off, Carty nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball on top of off. Hope tucks it to mid-wicket. Good end to the over but 11 runs off the over.
Dishes out a fuller ball on the slower side outside off. Hope pushes it to cover..
Short of a length and outside off, Carty plays it nicely to deep mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Wide! 10 runs already of the over. Too short and on middle, Carty ducks under it.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries! Poor delivery and punished! Jordan Neill tails this one on the hips. Carty tickles it to fine leg, fine past the fielder there for a boundary.
FOUR! A boundary after quite a while! Jordan Neill gives a lot of width, outside off. Carty slashes and hits it through covers for a boundary.
Angles it onto the pads. Hope helps it down to fine leg for a single.
On a length and on middle and leg. Carty tucks it to mid-wicket.
A good length delivery on top of off. Carty blocks it solidly.
Another run as Hope flicks this length ball to deep square leg.
Pulls his length back by a bit, outside off, Carty knocks it past cover for a single.
This away-angler delivery is working for Little so far. Goes full and outside off. Carty lets it go.
This is full and outside off, Hope guides it to third man for a single.
Angles in a length ball on middle, Hope tickles it behind square leg and keeps the strike.
Short again on off. Hope leaves but the umpires liked that one. Not given as a wide.
Wide! Not the best of starts from the debutants so far. Needs to be more accurate. Shorter and on leg, Hope leaves for a wide.
A bumper on middle and leg, Carty pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Dishes out a yorker angling on the pads. Hope works it past square leg for one more.
Wide! Goes short and across down the leg side. Hope looks to pull but misses.
Shapes it full and on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
West Indies have been watchful so far! Outside off on a length. Carty looks to punch but mistimes it back to the bowler.
Two runs off the over. A couple of good overs from Little. Short of a length, angled across, outside off. Hope slashes and misses.
Slightly short and around off, Carty hops and drops it through covers for a single.
Little goes short and into the surface on middle, Hope pulls it past mid-wicket for a run.
Three dots now! Goes full this time, it is outside off. Hope lets it go.
Josh Little gets close to the batter, a tad shorter and outside off. Hope looks to cut but misses it.
Shapes away a fuller delivery, outside off. Hope shoulders arms to it.
A single to end the over as Shai Hope bunts it past mid-wicket.
Short in length and around off, Hope taps it to the man at mid-wicket.
Wide! Bangs it short and well above Hope's head, it is left alone.
FOUR! Does not miss out this time. Pitched up, outside off. Hope just places it past cover and it races to the fence. Welcome boundary in this phase of cricket.
Hope misses out there. A gentle full toss on middle, Hope nudges it straight to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery, outside off. Hope knocks it to cover.
Leg bye! Slides in a full ball on the pads and it shapes in late, pings Carty on the pads as he looks to flick. It rolls to short fine leg for a leg bye.
Good end to the over! On a nagging length and on middle, Hope defends on his toes.
Length and on middle, this is nudged to mid-wicket for a single.
Excellent bowling! Bowls it into the surface, full and outside off. Carty looks to drive but misses.
Better line and length! Josh Little pulls his length back and bowls it outside off. Carty looks to cut it but misses.
Slants it across the batter, wide outside off. Hope leans to drive but inside edges it on the leg side for a single.
Wide! Fractionally short and around leg, Hope looks to pull it away but misses.
Josh Little steams in and serves it on a length and around off, angled across and it nips in. Hope mistimes his punch on the off side.
In the air and it falls short! Short of a length and outside off. Carty steps across to gently pull but gets a soft leading edge to mid on where it falls well short.
Short in length and on middle, Hope is slightly late as he pulls it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Good start for the visitors! Too straight from Jordan Neill, this is on middle, Hope drives it down the ground for a boundary.
Hard length delivery and it skids off the surface, around off, Hope blocks it out.
A good length ball, outside off, Carty dabs it to third man for a single.
Serves it full and on middle and leg. Carty flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! CARVED AWAY! Very full and outside off, Shai Hope leans on and drives it through covers for a cracking boundary to end the first Powerplay.
Little pulls back his length and bowls a shorter one, around off, Keacy hops up and drops it down to the left of cover for a quick single.
Swing and a miss! Touch full and well outside off, Keacy Carty strides forward and looks to drive it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Hard length and outside off, Keacy Carty watchfully leaves it.
On the pads and on a length, Carty shuffles across and tucks it to the left of deep fine leg for a couple of runs.
Good length and around off, Carty drops it down to cover.
WIDE! Starts off with a full ball, but way outside off, Keacy Carty leaves it. Called a wide.
Full and around off, Hope drives it straight to mid off.
Hard length and in that channel outside off, Shai Hope hops up a bit and cuts it hard but straight to backward point, who stops the ball, despite making a fumble.
This is better from Neill! Touch full and around off, invites the batter to play at it. Hope comes forward and drives it to cover.
Nagging length and around middle, Hope turns it down to mid-wicket.
FOUR! PULLED AWAY! That again shortish length and around off, Shai Hope goes back and muscles it over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary. Right off the middle of the bat! Also, 50 comes up for WI.
Debutant into the attack! Begins with a good-length ball, around off, Shai Hope blocks it off from the back foot.
Short of a length and well outside off, Keacy Carty leaves it alone.
Hard length and around off, Keacy Carty gets on the top of the bounce and drops it down towards cover.
Back of a length and around off, Carty gets inside the line and blocks it to the leg side.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! In the slot, around off, very full, Keacy Carty shifts his weight to the front foot and drives it in the gap to the left of cover point for a boundary.
Touch short and outside off, Keacy Carty cuts it but straight to backward point.
On a good length and around off, Keacy Carty defends it.
Nagging length and around off, Shai Hope drops it down towards cover.
FOUR! FLICKED AWAY! Too full and on the pads, a gift for the new batter and Shai Hope just lunges and whips it in the gap towards deep square leg for a boundary to get off the mark.
Back of a length and outside off, Shai Hope shoulders his arms.
Nagging length and around off, Shai Hope leaves it.
On a hard length and around off, Keacy Carty rides the bounce and turns it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! TOP SHOT! Right in the slot, very full and around middle, Keacy Carty comes forward and flicks it in the gap through square leg for a boundary.
Hard length and around off, Keacy Carty punches it aerially to the right of deep third man for a single.
WIDE! On a length and down the leg side, Keacy Carty misses his tickle shot and it is called a wide.
On a good length and around off, Keacy Carty punches it to cover.

On a good length and around off, seaming in, Keacy Carty looks to clip it to the leg side but gets a leading outside edge as the ball takes the extra bounce off the surface, but the ball goes on the bounce to the square leg fielder. No harm done.
A touch fuller and outside off, Keacy Carty leaves it.

An appeal for LBW but is turned down! Into the pitch, hard length and around middle, comes in with the angle, Keacy Carty looks to flick it but misses and wears it on the pads. Probably, going over the wickets.
Nagging length and around off, Keacy Carty defends it.

OUT! CAUGHT! A JUGGLING ACT AT THE SECOND SLIP! Slightly fuller and outside off, going away from the batter's arc, Evin Lewis just stands tall and throws his hands at it in order to cut it hard. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of the second slip, where Andy Balbirnie extends both his arms and tries to hold onto, but the ball pops out of his hands, and he grabs the catch in the third attempt.

Excellent effort to save one run for his side! Dragged length and on the pads, Keacy Carty flicks it towards deep backward square leg. Josh Little runs in to his left from deep fine leg and puts in a dive. He tried to flick it away as the motion was taking him over the ropes. He did well to get up and recollect the ball before throwing it to the keeper. After seeing a couple of replays, the third umpire is satisfied that he has done well there in the field to save one run. Three runs taken.
Good effort in the field! Over-pitched, around off, Keacy Carty drives it hard towards cover, where the fielder extends both his arms to his left and stops the ball.
BEAUTY! On a length and outside off, takes off from the surface and moves away as well. Keacy Carty looks to punch it to the off side but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Nagging length and around off, Keacy Carty leans on and drives it to cover.
Drags his length back a bit and attacks the stumps this time, Evin Lewis presses back and turns it to the left of mid-wicket for a quick single.

Play and a miss! From around the wicket, fuller and a bit outside off, gets it to swing away from the batter. Lewis shuffles and looks to drive it on the up but gets beaten on the outside edge. Lovely bowling!
Straight to the fielder! Full, in the slot and around off, Keacy Carty crouches and drives it hard but straight to extra cover.
Back of a length and over the top of the off stump, Keacy Carty hops up and drops it down towards cover.

On a length and around off, Evin Lewis drives it down the ground. The fielder from mid off runs in to his left and puts in a dive to cut it off. A single taken.

SIX! HOOKED AWAY! Back of a length and angles into the body of the batter, Evin Lewis moves in his crease, swivles on his toes and pulls it over the deep fine leg fence for a biggie.
Begins with a good-length ball, around off, Evin Lewis shuffles across and shoulders his arms to let it go to the keeper.

FOUR! OFF THE MARK IN STYLE! Touch full and around off, Keacy Carty leans on and creams the drive through covers for a boundary to open his account.

OUT! LBW! Barry McCarthy provides the early breakthrough for Ireland, and Brandon King is gone! On a length and attacks the stumps, gets an in-seam movement as this is bowled right from wide of the crease. Brandon King gets a bit late in bringing his bat down to flick it, and the ball beats the inside edge and pings him on the front pad. Barry McCarthy goes straightaway into an appeal and the Umpire obliges.

WIDE! Another one! This time it is on a fuller length but same line, down the leg side. King leaves it and it is called a wide as well.
WIDE! On a good length but down the leg side, gets a bit of inward seam movement. King watches it to go to the keeper and it is called a wide.
Both openers are underway now! Back of a length and around off, Evin Lewis goes back, rides the bounce and drops it down to the right of cover for a quick single.
